Almost there. Blerrie, what a job this one is going to be! I managed to dig up a little more intel with help from Joy. To get into the PEOC, you will need one of the special keycards they use. The most likely place to find one will be in the Oval Office.
There we go. I'll be nearby for when you need me.
And don't get too close to the Murkys. You may be using their uniforms, but these guys are the top of the crop and know their own.
Ooh, friends. Looks like rain is coming. Dont' want to ruin those nice Murky uniforms, so get inside.
That was easy enough. Not surprising, considering any old chop can get in!
OK, now get to the Oval Office in the West Wing. Find the access point.
Okay, first things first: You need to find access the oval office but its located in the West Wing. Find the access.
Those lights. Some kind of indicator. Look around and see if you can match them with anything.
Are you done with that gate yet?
There you go. Exciting, yeah?
That did the trick, good job, friends!
West Wing should be open to you now.
Did you make your way to the West Wing yet?
The Oval Office is close. The keycard you need to enter the PEOC should be there.
The Oval Office is right there. Get in there, friends.
OK now, they probably keep it in a safe. Find it.
Maybe hidden behind one of the paintings?
Ach! That's a Franz JÃ¤ger Mark II.
We're not going to get in there without the code. You'll have to find one.
You gotta find those codes. Search through some laptops.
With all the ruckus going on, I reckon the White House aids will have gotten sloppy. Maybe have a look in their computers to see if you can find something.
Ach, dwankie amateurs, keeping secure codes on USB sticks! Told you, didn't I? Have a look around and see if you can find it.
Found the USB stick yet? It's gotta be there somewhere.
There you go. Now, let's see whats on it.
You can use any laptop to extract the information.
Now enter the code in the safe.
Enter the code, friends. Have you forgotten it or something?
That's a keycard alright. Take it!
Alright. My data says that they keep a hidden access to the P.E.O.C. by the library. Get there and we should be able to use that damn keycard.
Reminder: (yada yada library)
Right, now my intel doesn't say exactly where the entrance is, so you'll have to rummage around a bit.
Maybe you gotta take down all the books, friends?
OK, that probably does something interesting. Try it.
That has to be the way into the PEOC. Get into the airlock.
How far down does this thing go? I hope our connection will hold.
OK, our pardons are locked in the vault. Have a closer look.
(sighs) This one looks familiar. We don't have liquid nitrogen, though. We need to work with what we've got. The pardons are in there.
I've got an idea. We hack the mainframe. We can probably get into it, even if there are several layers.
Friends, hook me up to the mainframe.
Keep an extra eye out for Murkys.
Almost done...
(cracks knuckles) Alright, I'm in. Give me a few minutes to disable the firewall.
There, all done. Enter the vault and let's get those pardons.
There's our prize. Bain will be happy. Take them and go!
What are you waiting for? Take all of them!
Stop idling around and get out of the PEOC!
Take off your masks and walk out of the front door. This will be the smoothest heist done yet so far.
